HOUSE BILL No. 1348
_____
DIGEST OF HB 1348 (Updated February 19, 2026 4:10 pm - DI 153)
Citations Affected: IC 8-1; IC 13-11; IC 13-18.
Synopsis: Regulation of grease control equipment. Establishes a
statewide regulatory scheme for grease control equipment. Provides
that a waste water treatment plant must continue to accept septage
under certain circumstances. Creates a process for septage haulers to
resolve disputes with wastewater treatment plants with respect to
accepting septage.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Pressel, Prescott, Morris, Baird
(SENATE SPONSORS — NIEMEYER, TOMES)
January 6, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Environmental Affairs.
January 22, 2026, amended, reported — Do Pass.
January 27, 2026, read second time, amended, ordered engrossed.
January 28, 2026, engrossed. Read third time, passed. Yeas 85, nays 1.
SENATE ACTION
February 2, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Environmental Affairs.
February 9, 2026, amended, reported favorably — Do Pass; reassigned to Committee on
Tax and Fiscal Policy.
February 17, 2026, reported favorably — Do Pass.
February 19, 2026, read second time, amended, ordered engrossed.
